  187: init_per_testcase(Func, Config) ->
  188:     CaseDir = filename:join(proplists:get_value(priv_dir, Config), Func),
  189:     ok = filelib:ensure_dir(filename:join([CaseDir, dummy_file])),
  190:     true = code:add_patha(CaseDir),
  191:     [{case_dir, CaseDir}|Config].
  192: 
  193: end_per_testcase(_Func, Config) ->
  194:     CaseDir = proplists:get_value(case_dir, Config),
  195:     unload_modules(CaseDir),
  196:     asn1_test_lib:rm_dirs([CaseDir]),
  197:     code:del_path(CaseDir).
  198: 
  199: unload_modules(CaseDir) ->
  200:     F = fun(Name0, Acc) ->
  201:                 Name1 = filename:rootname(filename:basename(Name0)),
  202:                 Name = list_to_existing_atom(Name1),
  203:                 [Name|Acc]
  204:         end,
  205:     Beams1 = lists:usort(filelib:fold_files(CaseDir, "[.]beam\$", true, F, [])),
  206:     Beams = [M || M <- Beams1, code:is_loaded(M) =/= false],
  207:     _ = [begin
  208:              code:purge(M),
  209:              code:delete(M),
  210:              code:purge(M),
  211:              io:format("Unloaded ~p", [M])
  212:          end || M <- Beams],
  213:     ok.

  215: %%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  216: %% Test runners
  217: %%------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  218: 
  219: have_jsonlib() ->
  220:     case code:which(jsx) of
  221:         non_existing -> false;
  222:     _ -> true
  223:     end.
  224: 
  225: test(Config, TestF) ->
  226:     TestJer = case have_jsonlib() of
  227:                   true -> [jer];
  228:                   false -> []
  229:               end,
  230:     test(Config, TestF, [per,
  231:                          uper,
  232:                          ber] ++ TestJer),
  233:     case TestJer of
  234:         [] -> {comment,"skipped JER"};
  235:         _ -> ok
  236:     end.
  237: 
  238: test(Config, TestF, Rules) ->
  239:     Fun = fun(C, R, O) ->
  240:                   M = element(2, erlang:fun_info(TestF, module)),
  241:                   F = element(2, erlang:fun_info(TestF, name)),
  242:                   io:format("Running ~p:~p with ~p...~n", [M, F, {R, O}]),
  243:                   try
  244:                       TestF(C, R, O)
  245:                   catch
  246:                       Class:Reason:Stk ->
  247:                           NewReason = {Reason, [{rule, R}, {options, O}]},
  248:                           erlang:raise(Class, NewReason, Stk)
  249:                   end
  250:           end,
  251:     Result = [run_case(Config, Fun, rule(Rule), opts(Rule)) || Rule <- Rules],
  252:     case lists:usort(Result) of
  253:         [true|_Skips] -> true; % At least one test ran
  254:         Skips        -> {skip, [R || {skip, R} <- Skips]} % All skipped
  255:     end.
  256: 
  257: rule(A) when is_atom(A) -> A;
  258: rule({A, _Opts} )       -> A.
  259: 
  260: opts(Rule) when is_atom(Rule) -> [];
  261: opts({_Rule, Opts})         -> Opts.
  262: 
  263: run_case(Config, Fun, Rule, Opts) ->
  264:     CaseDir = proplists:get_value(case_dir, Config),
  265:     Dir = filename:join([CaseDir, join(Rule, Opts)]),
  266:     ok = filelib:ensure_dir(filename:join([Dir, dummy_file])),
  267:     replace_path(CaseDir, Dir),
  268:     NewConfig = lists:keyreplace(case_dir, 1, Config, {case_dir, Dir}),
  269: 
  270:     % Run the actual test function
  271:     Result = Fun(NewConfig, Rule, Opts),
  272: 
  273:     replace_path(Dir, CaseDir),
  274:     case Result of
  275:         {skip, _Reason} -> Result;
  276:         _               -> true
  277:     end.
  278: 
  279: replace_path(PathA, PathB) ->
  280:     true = code:del_path(PathA),
  281:     true = code:add_patha(PathB).
  282: 
  283: join(Rule, Opts) ->
  284:     lists:join("_", [atom_to_list(Rule)|lists:map(fun atom_to_list/1, Opts)]).

  290: %% Cover run-time functions that are only called by the ASN.1 compiler
  291: %% (if any).
  292: cover(_) ->
  293:     Wc = filename:join([code:lib_dir(asn1),"ebin","asn1ct_eval_*.beam"]),
  294:     Beams = filelib:wildcard(Wc),
  295:     true = Beams =/= [],
  296:     [begin
  297: 	 M0 = filename:basename(Beam),
  298: 	 M1 = filename:rootname(M0),
  299: 	 M = list_to_atom(M1),
  300: 	 "asn1ct_eval_" ++ Group0 = M1,
  301: 	 Group = list_to_atom(Group0),
  302: 	 io:format("%%\n"
  303: 		   "%% ~s\n"
  304: 		   "%%\n", [M]),
  305: 	 asn1ct_func:start_link(),
  306: 	 [asn1ct_func:need({Group,F,A}) ||
  307: 	     {F,A} <- M:module_info(exports), F =/= module_info],
  308: 	 asn1ct_func:generate(group_leader())
  309:      end || Beam <- Beams],
  310:     ok.

  600: constraint_equivalence_abs(Config) ->
  601:     DataDir = proplists:get_value(data_dir, Config),
  602:     CaseDir = proplists:get_value(case_dir, Config),
  603:     Asn1Spec = "ConstraintEquivalence",
  604:     Asn1Src = filename:join(DataDir, Asn1Spec),
  605:     ok = asn1ct:compile(Asn1Src, [abs,{outdir,CaseDir}]),
  606:     AbsFile = filename:join(CaseDir, Asn1Spec++".abs"),
  607:     {ok,Terms} = file:consult(AbsFile),
  608:     Cs = [begin
  609: 	      Constraints = element(4, Type),
  610: 	      Name1 = atom_to_list(Name0),
  611: 	      {Name,_} = lists:splitwith(fun(C) -> C =/= $X end, Name1),
  612: 	      {Name,Constraints}
  613: 	  end || {typedef,_,_,Name0,Type} <- Terms],
  614:     R = sofs:relation(Cs, [{name,constraint}]),
  615:     F0 = sofs:relation_to_family(R),
  616:     F = sofs:to_external(F0),
  617:     Diff = [E || {_,L}=E <- F, length(L) > 1],
  618:     case Diff of
  619: 	[] ->
  620: 	    ok;
  621: 	[_|_] ->
  622: 	    io:put_chars("Not equivalent:\n"),
  623: 	    [io:format("~s: ~p\n", [N,D]) || {N,D} <- Diff],
  624: 	    ct:fail(length(Diff))
  625:     end.

 1388: xref(_Config) ->
 1389:     S = ?FUNCTION_NAME,
 1390:     xref:start(S),
 1391:     xref:set_default(S, [{verbose,false},{warnings,false},{builtins,true}]),
 1392:     Test = filename:dirname(code:which(?MODULE)),
 1393:     {ok,_PMs} = xref:add_directory(S, Test),
 1394:     Q = "X - XU - \".*_SUITE\" : Mod",
 1395:     UnusedExports = xref:q(S, Q),
 1396:     xref:stop(S),
 1397:     case UnusedExports of
 1398: 	{ok,[]} ->
 1399: 	    ok;
 1400: 	{ok,[_|_]=Res} ->
 1401: 	    ct:fail("Exported, but unused: ~p\n", [Res])
 1402:     end.

 1404: %% Ensure that all functions that are implicitly exported by
 1405: %% 'export_all' in this module are actually used.

 1407: xref_export_all(_Config) ->
 1408:     S = ?FUNCTION_NAME,
 1409:     xref:start(S),
 1410:     xref:set_default(S, [{verbose,false},{warnings,false},{builtins,true}]),
 1411:     {ok,_PMs} = xref:add_module(S, code:which(?MODULE)),
 1412:     AllCalled = all_called(),
 1413:     Def = "Called := " ++ lists:flatten(io_lib:format("~p", [AllCalled])),
 1414:     {ok,_} = xref:q(S, Def),
 1415:     {ok,Unused} = xref:q(S, "X - Called - range (closure E | Called)"),
 1416:     xref:stop(S),
 1417:     case Unused -- [{?MODULE,otp_14440_decode,0}] of
 1418:         [] ->
 1419:             ok;
 1420:         [_|_] ->
 1421:             Msg = [io_lib:format("~p:~p/~p\n", [M,F,A]) || {M,F,A} <- Unused],
 1422:             ct:fail("There are unused functions:\n\n~s\n", [Msg])
 1423:     end.
